# AKOS Evidence Class Gate

Use when a task **claims completion** on any governed surface: research source ledger,
closure UAT PASS, ACIM implementation cell, or initiative registry close.

Mechanical SSOT: [`akos/evidence_class_gate.py`](../../akos/evidence_class_gate.py).
Umbrella runbook: [`scripts/validate_evidence_class_gate.py`](../../scripts/validate_evidence_class_gate.py).
Vault doctrine (Operations PMO): [`EVIDENCE_CLASS_GATE_DISCIPLINE.md`](../../docs/references/hlk/v3.0/Admin/O5-1/Operations/PMO/canonicals/EVIDENCE_CLASS_GATE_DISCIPLINE.md)

Governance design: [`docs/wip/planning/90-routing-and-wiring/reports/evidence-class-gate-governance-design-2026-06-14.md`](../../docs/wip/planning/90-routing-and-wiring/reports/evidence-class-gate-governance-design-2026-06-14.md)

Pairs with skill [`evidence-class-gate-craft`](../../.cursor/skills/evidence-class-gate-craft/SKILL.md).

## RULE 1 — Pick proof class before PASS (binding)

Before setting `verdict: PASS` on a closure UAT (forward from 2026-06-14), set:

```yaml
evidence_class: <enum>
evidence_proof_ref: <repo-relative path>
```

`git_shape` alone is insufficient when the claim is experiential (UI, deploy, live data).

## RULE 2 — Research ledgers must be honest (binding)

Never mint hash-padded URL rows. One external base URL → one row. Run strip script after
bulk seed:

```powershell
py scripts/strip_padded_source_ledger.py --ledger <path> --write
py scripts/validate_research_action.py --source-ledger <path>
```

## RULE 3 — ACIM confirmed requires cite (binding)

`implemented` + `confirmed` with `last_review_at` ≥ 2026-06-14 needs `tool_catalog_ref`,
`realisation_refs`, or notes `evidence_class=` / `evidence_proof_ref=`.

## RULE 4 — Initiative close follows UAT evidence (binding)

Do not set `INITIATIVE_REGISTRY.status=closed` unless closure UAT PASS/PWF exists and PASS
rows satisfy RULE 1. Enforced by `validate_evidence_class_gate.py` for forward closes.

## RULE 5 — Finding-code allocation (binding)

- **UAT-FM-12** — PASS without evidence class (landed I90 P4)
- **UAT-FM-13** — sibling UI browser manifest (planned; do not reuse FM-12 slug)

